00:09:33.400 --> 00:09:36.590
RAMEZ NAAM: So Delgado went
on to write a book called

00:09:36.590 --> 00:09:40.020
Physical Control of the Mind,
Towards a Psychocivilized

00:09:40.020 --> 00:09:43.140
Society, where he posited that
we could improve society

00:09:43.140 --> 00:09:46.810
dramatically by fitting
criminals with brain implants

00:09:46.810 --> 00:09:49.860
that would cut off their
criminal urges, so on and so

00:09:49.860 --> 00:09:51.240
on and so forth.

00:09:51.240 --> 00:09:53.560
The medical community and
scientific community's

00:09:53.560 --> 00:09:54.960
response to this
was that it was

00:09:54.960 --> 00:09:57.200
extremely, extremely creepy.

00:09:57.200 --> 00:10:00.360
And can we please stop all
that and head on to some

00:10:00.360 --> 00:10:05.330
medical applications of this
tech, which they did.

00:10:05.330 --> 00:10:08.170
There's a TV show called House
with a doctor called House

00:10:08.170 --> 00:10:10.390
that solves all sorts of
crimes-- or all sorts of

00:10:10.390 --> 00:10:11.840
medical riddles, I think.

00:10:11.840 --> 00:10:14.960
Well the original Dr. House,
Dr. William House, was the

00:10:14.960 --> 00:10:17.540
first person to find a real
medical use for this

00:10:17.540 --> 00:10:18.370
technology.

00:10:18.370 --> 00:10:20.120
He invented the cochlear
implant.

00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:22.840
It looks like a hearing aid, but
it's for those people that

00:10:22.840 --> 00:10:25.270
have no hair cells
in the inner ear.

00:10:25.270 --> 00:10:27.570
So no hearing aid
can help them.

00:10:27.570 --> 00:10:30.170
Instead what it does is it
picks up sound of the

00:10:30.170 --> 00:10:31.150
microphone.

00:10:31.150 --> 00:10:34.510
It has a small compute that
does a re-encoding, if you

00:10:34.510 --> 00:10:39.470
will, from vibrations
into nerve impulses.

00:10:39.470 --> 00:10:44.090
And then it electrically
stimulates the nerves of the

00:10:44.090 --> 00:10:46.780
inner ear, the auditory
nerve fiber.

00:10:46.780 --> 00:10:48.920
And that causes people
to hear.

00:10:48.920 --> 00:10:53.080
The auditory nerve has 30,000
neurons in it on each side.

00:10:53.080 --> 00:10:55.710
And the first cochlear implant
had one electrode.

00:10:55.710 --> 00:10:58.610
The best ones implanted in
people today have 23.

00:10:58.610 --> 00:11:00.270
So you wouldn't think it
could work at all.

00:11:00.270 --> 00:11:04.010
But it actually produces hearing
that is not as good as

00:11:04.010 --> 00:11:08.050
a normal person's, but is enough
that they can read--

00:11:08.050 --> 00:11:10.260
can hear what people are
saying and interpret it

00:11:10.260 --> 00:11:11.930
without reading lips.

00:11:11.930 --> 00:11:13.800
And it has been life changing.

00:11:13.800 --> 00:11:17.550
About 200,000 people around
the world have this today.

00:11:17.550 --> 00:11:19.600
This is the picture an
eight-year-old girl hearing

00:11:19.600 --> 00:11:20.540
for the first time.

00:11:20.540 --> 00:11:23.380
And I'm going to show you a
